        android:text="1) Increase your calorie intake: You need to consume more calories than you burn to gain weight. Try to add an extra 500 to 1000 calories to your daily diet.\n\n

2) Choose nutrient-dense foods: Eat foods that are high in nutrients such as protein, complex carbohydrates, healthy fats, and vitamins and minerals. Examples include lean meats, fish, beans, nuts, seeds, whole grains, fruits, and vegetables.\n\n

3)Eat frequently: Try to eat small meals and snacks throughout the day, instead of three large meals. This can help increase your calorie intake.\n\n

4) Exercise regularly: Incorporate strength training exercises into your routine to help build muscle mass. This can help you gain weight in a healthy way.\n\n

